First, we'll introduce a new function. Last time, we explored the console; this time, we want to get input. We'll do this by the <code>prompt()</code> function. On the right is an example of it in action! <br> We're going to use an <code>if</code> statement in this example and do two different things, depending on whether the user is "of age" or not. <pre><code>if (prompt("How old are you?") >= 21) {
    alert("You can drink! Here's a toast!");
} else {
    alert("You're too young; get out of my bar!");
}</code></pre>
